Look like very different logic - use different MSR.

I think FreeBSD's coretemp have incorrect check of tjmax for Conroe.

I'll do more test a bit later with Linux and FreeBSD on different CPUs - Core 2 Duo E6xxx/E4xxx, Pentium Dual-Core E2xxx, and on Wolfdale Core 2 Duo E7xxx.

I want to try, but I can't promise to do this: apply Linux's logic with MSR 0x17 (MSR_IA32_PLATFORM_ID) to coretemp and test it on my hardware.

P.S. I hope my poor english won't hurt to understand me…
